# Nakhi, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Nakhi () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Nakhkinsky Selsoviet, Akushinsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 415 as of 2010. There are 3 streets.
Geography
Nakhi is located 36&nbsp;km southeast of Akusha (the district's administrative centre) by road, on the Dargolakotta River. Natsi is the nearest rural locality.
